      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be a commercially validated code with documented V&V procedures and version control at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used under ISO 9001-certified QMS. Software version control, release notes, and regression test suite documentation confirm Gradation 2 compliance. No custom solver modifications were introduced."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via benchmark test cases at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Verification against FDA benchmark nozzle flow and lid-driven cavity cases confirmed solver accuracy. Residual convergence criteria of 1e-6 applied uniformly. Order-of-accuracy testing confirmed second-order spatial convergence for momentum equations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported and discretization error bounded below 5% at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.4M, fine 12.8M cells). GCI calculated per Celik et al. (2008). Fine-to-medium GCI for hemolysis index quantity of interest was 2.3%, within the 5% acceptance threshold. Medium mesh selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to the COU operating envelope at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark experiments conducted at flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at rotational speeds of 2000–3500 RPM, fully encompassing the CPB operating envelope. Temperature, fluid properties (bovine blood, 37°C, hematocrit 35%), and boundary conditions are documented in the study protocol and traceable to ISO 10993-4 test methods."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted QoI must be compared quantitatively to experimental data with defined agreement metrics at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by CFD compared against experimental plasma-free hemoglobin measurements. Mean absolute percentage error of 8.4% across all 5 operating points. All predicted RH values remained below 1.0, consistent with acceptance criterion. Agreement deemed satisfactory for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI must be directly relevant to the clinical decision and hemolysis risk characterization at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB device hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Scalar hemolysis index integrated over flow volume captures cumulative blood damage relevant to clinical outcomes. QoI selection is directly tied to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on geometry and conditions sufficiently representative of the COU device and operating range at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same platform as the COU device family. Operating conditions span the full CPB clinical range. Fluid properties match COU (bovine blood as surrogate per FDA guidance). Validation scenario is assessed as directly applicable to the COU without extrapolation beyond the validation domain."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires acknowledgment that solver round-off and iterative errors exist; formal quantification not required.",
      "rationale": "Solver iterative convergence monitored via residuals (all below 1e-6) and force/moment monitors stabilized to <0.1% variation over final 500 iterations. Round-off error not formally quantified; acceptable at MRL 2 Gradation 1 given double-precision arithmetic throughout."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
