      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires that simulation setup be performed by qualified personnel; formal use-error analysis not required.",
      "rationale": "Simulations executed by PhD-level CFD engineers with >5 years rotodynamic pump simulation experience. Peer review of simulation setup performed internally. Formal use-error FMEA not conducted; consistent with Gradation 1 requirements at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires that model form assumptions be documented; uncertainty quantification of model form error not required.",
      "rationale": "RANS k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published literature for rotary blood pump hemolysis prediction. Power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen et al.) applied. Model form assumptions documented in simulation report. Formal model form UQ deferred per MRL 2 Gradation 1 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires that input parameters be identified and sourced; formal sensitivity analysis not required.",
      "rationale": "Key model inputs identified: fluid viscosity, density, hematocrit, hemolysis power-law coefficients (alpha, beta), rotational speed, and flow boundary conditions. Sources documented (ISO 10993-4, published literature, device specifications). Input sensitivity analysis not performed; consistent with Gradation 1 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires that test sample characteristics be documented; statistical characterization of sample variability not required.",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation used n=3 pump units per operating condition. Unit-to-unit geometric variability estimated at <0.5% based on manufacturing tolerances. Blood analog preparation documented per ASTM F1841. Statistical characterization of inter-sample variability not performed; acceptable at Gradation 1 MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 requires that differences between simulation inputs and experimental conditions be identified; formal equivalency analysis not required.",
      "rationale": "Differences between simulation inputs and experimental conditions noted: CFD uses steady-state MRF rotation approximation vs. actual transient impeller motion; bovine blood viscosity used in experiment vs. Newtonian fluid assumption in CFD. Differences documented and judged acceptable for Gradation 1 at MRL 2 given prior literature precedent for these approximations in hemolysis prediction."
    }
